@vrothberg you worked on the "cp crossing mountpoint boundry" thing.  I'm wondering if this issue is (somehow) a consequence of that?  Specifically - suggesting why this only happens in Ubuntu and never Fedora.

Also, I'm wondering if perhaps a "easy" solution could be to make "podman cp" always skip trying to read `/proc`, `/sys`, and `/dev` inside the container.  I can't think of any reason why directories down those trees would ***ever*** be useful to copy to any other context.

What's your take?

Sigh...maybe we need this too just to be safe:

